[Also read The Atlantic article, How Long Does Omicron Take to Make You Sick? The new variant seems to be our quickest one yet. That makes it harder to catch with the tests we have.
https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2021/12/omicron-incubation-period-testing/621066/ by Katherine J. Wu.

"Estimates for this exposure-to-symptom gap, called the incubation period, clocked in at about 5 days for alpha and 4 days for delta. Now word has it that the newest kid on the pandemic block, omicron, may have ratcheted it down to as little as 3." - Mod.LK]

